alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - High Coolant Temperature
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. The coolant level is low, causing a high coolant temperature issue. 2. The radiator external core may be plugged with foreign material and should be checked and thoroughly cleaned. 3. The engine cooling fan may not be operating correctly, verify fan operation. 4. Internal engine issues such as coolant pump failure, Head gasket failure, EGR cooler issues etc. 5.  On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Water in Fuel System Fault
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine water in fuel concern.   This situation only applies to Diesel engine trucks.  Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, the driver to visually check the fuel water separator for water in fuel.  If water is visible he may be able to drain the water from the filter as allowed by local restrictions.  Additional actions. Verify that the fuel water filter has been serviced, especially prior to winter operation.  The issue may be caused by a faulty fuel / water sensor, check and replace as required.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Engine Cylinder Miss Fire
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine miss situation.   Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, ask the driver to verify the fuel level.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  Some causes of engine miss fire are:  1. Faulty spark plugs.  2. Faulty Coils.  3. Faulty spark plug wires.  4. Faulty ICM.  5. Fuel system valve or sensor issues.  6. Internal engine failure.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Coolant Issues
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine coolant concern code.   Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or notices a higher than normal coolant temperature. Have the driver verify that the coolant reservoir is at the correct level.  DO NOT tell the driver to remove the coolant Radiator cap to add coolant if low. Additional actions.  Technician will have to verify high coolant temperature situation or low coolant level.  Issues to check are leaking hoses or external cooling system leaks. Fan Belt worn or failed, Coolant pump failure, Low coolant level, plugged radiator core, verify behind the CAC. Incorrect antifreeze mix, EGR related issues.  More diagnostics will be necessary.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - High Coolant Temperature
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. The coolant level is low, causing a high coolant temperature issue. 2. The radiator external core may be plugged with foreign material and should be checked and thoroughly cleaned. 3. The engine cooling fan may not be operating correctly, verify fan operation. 4. Internal engine issues such as coolant pump failure, Head gasket failure, EGR cooler issues etc. 5.  On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine miss situation.   Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, ask the driver to verify the fuel level.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  Some causes of engine miss fire are:  1. Faulty spark plugs.  2. Faulty Coils.  3. Faulty spark plug wires.  4. Faulty ICM.  5. Fuel system valve or sensor issues.  6. Internal engine failure.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Water in Fuel System Fault
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine water in fuel concern.   This situation only applies to Diesel engine trucks.  Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, the driver to visually check the fuel water separator for water in fuel.  If water is visible he may be able to drain the water from the filter as allowed by local restrictions.  Additional actions. Verify that the fuel water filter has been serviced, especially prior to winter operation.  The issue may be caused by a faulty fuel / water sensor, check and replace as required.

alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine miss situation.   Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, ask the driver to verify the fuel level.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  Some causes of engine miss fire are:  1. Faulty spark plugs.  2. Faulty Coils.  3. Faulty spark plug wires.  4. Faulty ICM.  5. Fuel system valve or sensor issues.  6. Internal engine failure.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Water in Fuel System Fault
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine water in fuel concern.   This situation only applies to Diesel engine trucks.  Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, the driver to visually check the fuel water separator for water in fuel.  If water is visible he may be able to drain the water from the filter as allowed by local restrictions.  Additional actions. Verify that the fuel water filter has been serviced, especially prior to winter operation.  The issue may be caused by a faulty fuel / water sensor, check and replace as required.

alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - High Coolant Temperature
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. The coolant level is low, causing a high coolant temperature issue. 2. The radiator external core may be plugged with foreign material and should be checked and thoroughly cleaned. 3. The engine cooling fan may not be operating correctly, verify fan operation. 4. Internal engine issues such as coolant pump failure, Head gasket failure, EGR cooler issues etc. 5.  On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Water in Fuel System Fault
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine water in fuel concern.   This situation only applies to Diesel engine trucks.  Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, the driver to visually check the fuel water separator for water in fuel.  If water is visible he may be able to drain the water from the filter as allowed by local restrictions.  Additional actions. Verify that the fuel water filter has been serviced, especially prior to winter operation.  The issue may be caused by a faulty fuel / water sensor, check and replace as required.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Engine Cylinder Miss Fire
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine miss situation.   Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, ask the driver to verify the fuel level.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  Some causes of engine miss fire are:  1. Faulty spark plugs.  2. Faulty Coils.  3. Faulty spark plug wires.  4. Faulty ICM.  5. Fuel system valve or sensor issues.  6. Internal engine failure.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Low Oil Pressure
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a low engine oil pressure concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing an engine warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  Possible causes are:  1. Engine oil level is low, Verify engine oil level.  2. Engine oil pressure sensor is faulty.  Verify actual engine oil pressure with manual gauge. If manual verification verifies that the oil pressure is at manufacturer specification then replace the oil pressure sensor. 3. If the manual oil pressure verifies that the oil pressure is low then additional internal engine diagnostics as to the cause of low oil pressure will be required.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - High Coolant Temperature
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. The coolant level is low, causing a high coolant temperature issue. 2. The radiator external core may be plugged with foreign material and should be checked and thoroughly cleaned. 3. The engine cooling fan may not be operating correctly, verify fan operation. 4. Internal engine issues such as coolant pump failure, Head gasket failure, EGR cooler issues etc. 5.  On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - High Coolant Temperature
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting a high coolant temperature concern. Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light.  Additional actions.  Check specific code information for actual fault code diagnosis tree in Engine diagnostics software.  The cause may be one of these five items.  1. The coolant level is low, causing a high coolant temperature issue. 2. The radiator external core may be plugged with foreign material and should be checked and thoroughly cleaned. 3. The engine cooling fan may not be operating correctly, verify fan operation. 4. Internal engine issues such as coolant pump failure, Head gasket failure, EGR cooler issues etc. 5.  On engines where the coolant pump is driven by the fan belt there may be fan belt issues. Check and verify fan belt condition.

alertRule.subject: Vehicle Alert - Water in Fuel System Fault
alertRule.message: Fault Concern.  This vehicle is transmitting an engine water in fuel concern.   This situation only applies to Diesel engine trucks.  Contact the driver and verify if he is seeing a warning light or feels a lack of power. If yes, the driver to visually check the fuel water separator for water in fuel.  If water is visible he may be able to drain the water from the filter as allowed by local restrictions.  Additional actions. Verify that the fuel water filter has been serviced, especially prior to winter operation.  The issue may be caused by a faulty fuel / water sensor, check and replace as required.
